  "commentary": "**Dealer Hedging Commentary:**\n\nWith SPX at 6822 sitting just below the max positive gamma wall at 6830 (102B), dealers are in active selling mode to hedge their long gamma positions as spot approaches this key resistance level. The PIN regime with massive positive GEX concentration between 6810-6840 creates a strong gravitational pull that should cap upside momentum and encourage mean reversion back toward the 6800-6820 range. The -0.4% 5-minute pullback suggests the 6830 gamma wall is already providing resistance, with dealers likely stepping up their hedging flow as expected.\n\nKey levels: 6830 resistance (max positive gamma), 6747 GEX flip as downside pivot, and the 6820-6825 zone as the core stabilization range.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect price to get capped near 6830 and grind sideways between 6810-6830.",
